<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   PARIS -- France's current account balance of payments
surplus widened in March to 1.33 billion francs ($241
million) from a revised surplus of 826 million francs in
February, according to seasonally adjusted figures released
by the Economics Ministry.
   February's figure was revised downward from a previously
estimated surplus of 1.9 billion francs, and brought the
accumulated surplus for the first three months of this year
to 5.47 billion francs, down from a surplus of 9.93 billion
francs in the same 1989 period.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   On an unadjusted basis, the French current account showed
a surplus of 883 million francs in March, compared with a
deficit of 4.12 billion francs in February.
