<IN>
INITIAL STOCK OFFERINGS (INI)
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
</IN>
<LP>
   LIDAK PHARMACEUTICALS said it completed its initial public
offering of one million units at $5 each. Each unit consists
of five common shares and five redeemable Class A warrants.
Each Class A warrant is exercisable to buy one common share
and one redeemable Class B warrant at $1.50 until May 8,
1995. Each Class B warrant holder may buy one common share at
$2.25 until May 8, 1995. D.H. Blair &amp; Co. managed the
underwriters, the La Jolla, Calif., company said. Proceeds
will be used to fund human clinical trials of a therapeutic
product to treat herpes and certain inflammatory skin
disorders and for research and development of other
pharmaceutical products.
