   Business Brief -- Boulevard Bancorp Inc.:
   Work Force Cut to Result
   In a Second-Quarter Charge
</HL>
<DATE>
05/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   BLVD
</CO>
<LP>
   Boulevard Bancorp Inc. said it will take a $650,000 charge
against its second-quarter earnings as a result of a 10%
reduction in its work force.
   The Chicago-based bank holding company, which has assets
of $1.7 billion, has about 865 employees.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Boulevard said the reduction is one of several actions it
is taking to improve long-term profitability and shareholder
returns. The company said it expects the measures to result
in annual savings of between $2 million to $2.5 million.
   In the year-earlier quarter, Boulevard earned $2.5
million, or 39 cents a share.
