<HL>
   Business Brief -- Loral Corp.:
   Firm Posts Flat Earnings
   For Fiscal Fourth Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
05/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   LOR
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<LP>
   Loral Corp. reported flat net income for its fiscal fourth
quarter, but fourth-quarter earnings from continuing
operations jumped 49% from a year ago.
   The New York-based defense electronics concern said it
earned $25.1 million, or $1 a share, in the latest
three-month period ended March 31, the same as in its
year-earlier fourth quarter.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   All of this year's fourth-quarter net income was from
continuing operations. In the year-ago period, however, the
company earned $16.8 million, or 67 cents a share on
continuing operations, and $8.3 million, or 33 cents a share,
on discontinued operations.
   Sales rose 36% to $444.7 million, from $326.8 million in
the quarter.
   For the full fiscal year, Loral earned $78.2 million, or
$3.11 a share, down 11% from $87.6 million, or $3.50 a share.
On continuing operations, earnings for the fiscal 12 months
rose 28% to $77.5 million, or $3.08 a share, from $60.3
million, or $2.41 a share.
   Results for the latest full year include a $10.5 million
pretax charge covering costs related to the company's guilty
plea to charges arising from a Justice Department
investigation into Pentagon contracting abuses.
   Sales for the 12 months climbed 6.7% to $1.27 billion from
$1.19 billion.
</TEXT>
